<br>
The Alliance has had a Raid scheduled for today now for quite some time on the Events Calendar. In-house. We, as a guild and group of guilds have been looking forward to this. I was sent some tells from folks that got there early that it looked like a raid was already heading up there. I got a quick port over and found out who was leading it.<br>
<br>
I informed the leader of our scheduled event and he seemed to not be very interested stating that they wouldn't be up there but only a few hours and wouldn't be killing the entire zone. That's not the point. there are 8 hour timers on most of the MOBs up there. This raid was getting ready to port up 2 and a half hours before the Alliance was scheduled to go up.<br>
<br>
After stating the facts to the Raid party in shout, and informing them of the Event Calendar and such, alot of folks honorably backed out and sent me tells stating such. I cannot tell you how much that is appreciated and how much that helps polish the name you make for yourself in this game by showing such honor. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The raid was eventually cancelled by the leader, due to a number of folks finally backing out.<br>
<br>
To all those innocent folks that were looking forward to going and enjoying a hate raid... some of you, your FIRST Hate raid... I personally apologize. Again, I truly mean that.<br>
<br>
If this server is to remain somewhat civilized, given the facts we have to deal with laid down by Verant, then we must all respect the Calendar as best we can. I appreciate the folks that did today. I respect you.<br>
<br>
Had this other Raid leader organized his Open raid say... 6-8 hours before we were to head up, then I'd have come into SRo and personally wished them good fortuen and luck on nice drops. It wouldn't have interfered wish our raid at all. But 2 and a half hours before ours... That's not gonna work in a Zone like the planes. Either he is new to Hate, or just didn't care. I don't know.<br>
<br>
In any event, I again apologize for ruining a good portion of a Saturday for some of you. I truly feel aweful about it. You should know that you did the right thing though, and went a long way toward continuing to keep this a good and respected Server.<br>
<br>
